<h1>Muse - the district is your canvas</h1>
<div class="project-image section">
    <img src="img/muse-landing.jpg">
</div>
<div class="project-description section">
  <strong class="role-title">Role:</strong> 
  <ul class="role">
    <li>App Development, Design, Concept, UI/UX, &amp; Photography</li>
    <li>Madeline Beard: Design, Concept, UI/UX, Photography, Landing page development</li>
    <li>Josh Mahan: Design, Concept, UI/UX, Branding</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="problem">
    <p><em>Problem:</em> People are impatient and bored waiting for public transportation in Washington, DC.</p>
    <p><em>Solution:</em> Create an app to occupy time creatively.</p>
  </div>

  <p>Given the problem, we decided to create Muse. Muse is a web-app that makes every commute a creative experience while also bringing public, user-generated art to DC's metro stations.</p>

  <p>Each week users are given a theme based on a quote from a DC native. Using this theme as a guide, each user can create their own works of art while traveling through the metro. Submitted works can be favorited by users on the gallery page. The more "likes" a submitted work gets, the larger the image appears on "digital canvases", set up in metro stations across the city.</p>

  <a class="live" target="_blank" href="http://allypalanzi.github.io/districtmuse/landing/">View Landing Page</a>
</div>
<h3>Research, UI/UX, and User Testing</h3>
<div class="project-description section">
  <p>First, we started by sending out a survey to see what people spent their time doing while waiting for the metro. The results were clear: most spent the time browsing on their smartphones.</p>
</div>

<div class="project-image section">
    <img src="img/muse-flowchart-crop.png">
    <cite>Click to view full size <a href="/img/muse-flowchart.png">here</a>.</cite>
</div>
<div class="project-description section">
  <p>We then began to break down the app and figure out exactly what we wanted it to do. Users can see the theme, check-in to the metro station they are waiting at, draw an image, and rate other users images in the gallery.</p>
</div>

<div class="project-image section">
